      "writtenOn": "2026-07-22T11:14:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "According to Section 10.6 (\u0027FRU Record Table carriage\u0027) of the DSP0257 \nspecification, each fragmented response (chunk) contains 0 to 3 bytes of padding and a 4-byte checksum at the end.\n\nAs far as I understand, `fru_record_table_data` and `fru_record_table_length` include this padding and checksum. If so, appending them via .insert() will leave intermediate CRC and padding bytes inside the final table, which will break `FRUTablePrint` parsing (and likely cause a segfault). \n\nI think we need to strip the padding and checksum from each chunk before accumulating the data.",
